In September, the team and I had the opportunity to return to the Monaco Yacht Show!

We’ve been attending Monaco Yacht Show for the last 4 years using it as an opportunity to film content and showcase assets aside from real estate. In the past we tried to fit as many yacht tours as possible but soon realized how this took away from the core essence of why we want to come to these shows in the first place. 

While we love showcasing the yachts, we wanted to highlight something deeper: the yachting industry itself.

Luxury often feels exclusive, but events like the Monaco Yacht Show serve as a bridge, sparking conversations and creating opportunities that might otherwise feel out of reach. The relationships we’ve built here with shipyards, brokerages, and owner representatives, they don’t happen overnight. They’re nurtured over time, laying the groundwork for future collaborations and deeper insights into the industry.

The lessons we’ve taken away are universal:
 • Immerse yourself in the field you’re passionate about
 • Build relationships with the people driving innovation and progress 
 • Learn from their experiences and apply those lessons to your own journey with constant focus on expanding your knowledge.

We’re aware there’s only so much we can say without actually SEEING the show firsthand. That’s why we filmed a full behind the scenes vlog to bring you along and get an in depth look into how we prepare, who we meet, the friends we bring along the way, and SO much more! 

The full vlog is on the Enes Plus channel, make sure to check it out, and let us know what you think of the new format we’re trying. We’re always open to your feedback :)
